SEQ(1)                         User Commands                         SEQ(1)

NAME
    seq - print a sequence of numbers

SYNOPSIS
    seq [OPTION]... LAST
    seq [OPTION]... FIRST LAST
    seq [OPTION]... FIRST INCREMENT LAST

DESCRIPTION
    Print numbers from FIRST to LAST, stepping by INCREMENT, one per line.
    FIRST and INCREMENT default to 1. Values may be floating-point; the
    generator uses C-locale long-double arithmetic, so a decimal point is
    always '.' regardless of any locale.

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils seq(1), ported to Horus and run as a
    ring-3 program from /bin/seq.

OPTIONS
    -s STRING    separate numbers with STRING (default: newline)
    -w           pad numbers with leading zeros to equal width
    -f FORMAT    use printf-style floating FORMAT

    Run `seq --help` for the full option list.

EXIT STATUS
    0 on success, non-zero on a malformed argument.

SEE ALSO
    printf(1), wc(1), hier(7)
